5.4. Structural Model Analysis
Table 5 displays the outcomes of the correlations among the construct variables, path coefficients (β), T-Statistics, and associated p-values. These results were obtained through the use of PLS algorithms, which enabled the evaluation of the structural relationships between model constructs and the testing of the research hypotheses. The analysis also included the Bootstrapping and Blindfolding procedures performed within SmartPLS4 with 1000 iterations.
